
[1]alteration

   ALTERA'TION, n. [L. alteratio.]

   The act of making different, or of varying in some particular; an
   altering or partial change; also the change made, or the loss or
   acquisition of qualities not essential to the form or nature of a
   thing. Thus a cold substance suffers an alteration when it becomes hot.
